00869 /* ##########################   NVIC functions  #################################### */
00887 static __INLINE void NVIC_SetPriorityGrouping(uint32_t PriorityGroup)
00888 {
00889   uint32_t reg_value;
00890   uint32_t PriorityGroupTmp = (PriorityGroup & 0x07);                         /* only values 0..7 are used          */
00891 
00892   reg_value  =  SCB->AIRCR;                                                   /* read old register configuration    */
00893   reg_value &= ~(SCB_AIRCR_VECTKEY_Msk | SCB_AIRCR_PRIGROUP_Msk);             /* clear bits to change               */
00894   reg_value  =  (reg_value                       |
00895                 (0x5FA << SCB_AIRCR_VECTKEY_Pos) |
00896                 (PriorityGroupTmp << 8));                                     /* Insert write key and priorty group */
00897   SCB->AIRCR =  reg_value;
00898 }
00899

00908 static __INLINE uint32_t NVIC_GetPriorityGrouping(void)
00909 {
00910   return ((SCB->AIRCR & SCB_AIRCR_PRIGROUP_Msk) >> SCB_AIRCR_PRIGROUP_Pos);   /* read priority grouping field */
00911 }

01005 static __INLINE void NVIC_SetPriority(IRQn_Type IRQn, uint32_t priority)
01006 {
01007   if(IRQn < 0) {
01008     SCB->SHP[((uint32_t)(IRQn) & 0xF)-4] = ((priority << (8 - __NVIC_PRIO_BITS)) & 0xff); } /* set Priority for Cortex-M  System Interrupts */
01009   else {
01010     NVIC->IP[(uint32_t)(IRQn)] = ((priority << (8 - __NVIC_PRIO_BITS)) & 0xff);    }        /* set Priority for device specific Interrupts  */
01011 }

01050 static __INLINE uint32_t NVIC_EncodePriority (uint32_t PriorityGroup, uint32_t PreemptPriority, uint32_t SubPriority)
01051 {
01052   uint32_t PriorityGroupTmp = (PriorityGroup & 0x07);          /* only values 0..7 are used          */
01053   uint32_t PreemptPriorityBits;
01054   uint32_t SubPriorityBits;
01055 
01056   PreemptPriorityBits = ((7 - PriorityGroupTmp) > __NVIC_PRIO_BITS) ? __NVIC_PRIO_BITS : 7 - PriorityGroupTmp;
01057   SubPriorityBits     = ((PriorityGroupTmp + __NVIC_PRIO_BITS) < 7) ? 0 : PriorityGroupTmp - 7 + __NVIC_PRIO_BITS;
01058 
01059   return (
01060            ((PreemptPriority & ((1 << (PreemptPriorityBits)) - 1)) << SubPriorityBits) |
01061            ((SubPriority     & ((1 << (SubPriorityBits    )) - 1)))
01062          );
01063 }
01064

01080 static __INLINE void NVIC_DecodePriority (uint32_t Priority, uint32_t PriorityGroup, uint32_t* pPreemptPriority, uint32_t* pSubPriority)
01081 {
01082   uint32_t PriorityGroupTmp = (PriorityGroup & 0x07);          /* only values 0..7 are used          */
01083   uint32_t PreemptPriorityBits;
01084   uint32_t SubPriorityBits;
01085 
01086   PreemptPriorityBits = ((7 - PriorityGroupTmp) > __NVIC_PRIO_BITS) ? __NVIC_PRIO_BITS : 7 - PriorityGroupTmp;
01087   SubPriorityBits     = ((PriorityGroupTmp + __NVIC_PRIO_BITS) < 7) ? 0 : PriorityGroupTmp - 7 + __NVIC_PRIO_BITS;
01088 
01089   *pPreemptPriority = (Priority >> SubPriorityBits) & ((1 << (PreemptPriorityBits)) - 1);
01090   *pSubPriority     = (Priority                   ) & ((1 << (SubPriorityBits    )) - 1);
01091 }

01098 static __INLINE void NVIC_SystemReset(void)
01099 {
01100   __DSB();                                                     /* Ensure all outstanding memory accesses included
01101                                                                   buffered write are completed before reset */
01102   SCB->AIRCR  = ((0x5FA << SCB_AIRCR_VECTKEY_Pos)      |
01103                  (SCB->AIRCR & SCB_AIRCR_PRIGROUP_Msk) |
01104                  SCB_AIRCR_SYSRESETREQ_Msk);                   /* Keep priority group unchanged */
01105   __DSB();                                                     /* Ensure completion of memory access */
01106   while(1);                                                    /* wait until reset */
01107 }

01134 static __INLINE uint32_t SysTick_Config(uint32_t ticks)
01135 {
01136   if (ticks > SysTick_LOAD_RELOAD_Msk)  return (1);            /* Reload value impossible */
01137 
01138   SysTick->LOAD  = (ticks & SysTick_LOAD_RELOAD_Msk) - 1;      /* set reload register */
01139   NVIC_SetPriority (SysTick_IRQn, (1<<__NVIC_PRIO_BITS) - 1);  /* set Priority for Cortex-M0 System Interrupts */
01140   SysTick->VAL   = 0;                                          /* Load the SysTick Counter Value */
01141   SysTick->CTRL  = SysTick_CTRL_CLKSOURCE_Msk |
01142                    SysTick_CTRL_TICKINT_Msk   |
01143                    SysTick_CTRL_ENABLE_Msk;                    /* Enable SysTick IRQ and SysTick Timer */
01144   return (0);                                                  /* Function successful */
01145 }

01172 static __INLINE uint32_t ITM_SendChar (uint32_t ch)
01173 {
01174   if ((CoreDebug->DEMCR & CoreDebug_DEMCR_TRCENA_Msk)  &&      /* Trace enabled */
01175       (ITM->TCR & ITM_TCR_ITMENA_Msk)                  &&      /* ITM enabled */
01176       (ITM->TER & (1UL << 0)        )                    )     /* ITM Port #0 enabled */
01177   {
01178     while (ITM->PORT[0].u32 == 0);
01179     ITM->PORT[0].u8 = (uint8_t) ch;
01180   }
01181   return (ch);
01182 }

01194 static __INLINE int32_t ITM_ReceiveChar (void) {
01195   int32_t ch = -1;                           /* no character available */
01196 
01197   if (ITM_RxBuffer != ITM_RXBUFFER_EMPTY) {
01198     ch = ITM_RxBuffer;
01199     ITM_RxBuffer = ITM_RXBUFFER_EMPTY;       /* ready for next character */
01200   }
01201 
01202   return (ch);
01203 }

01215 
01216   if (ITM_RxBuffer == ITM_RXBUFFER_EMPTY) {
01217     return (0);                                 /* no character available */
01218   } else {
01219     return (1);                                 /*    character available */
01220   }
